<sect2 id="gimp-layer-duplicate">
  <title>Duplicate layers</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Layer</primary>
    <secondary>Stack managing</secondary>
    <tertiary>Layer duplicate</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Duplicate Layers</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <para>
    The <guimenuitem>Duplicate Layers</guimenuitem> command adds a copy of
    each selected layer to the image.
    The name of each new layer is the same as the name of the original layer,
    but with <quote>copy</quote> or a number appended to it.
  </para>
  <para>
    Note that if there are any <link linkend="glossary-parasite">parasites</link>
    attached to the selected layers, they are not duplicated.
  </para>

  <sect3>
    <title>Activating the Command</title>
    <para>
      You can access this command
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           From the main menu through
          <menuchoice>
            <guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
            <guimenuitem>Duplicate Layers</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           By using the keyboard shortcut
           <keycombo>
              <keycap>Shift</keycap>
              <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
              <keycap>D</keycap>
            </keycombo>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          From the
          <link linkend="gimp-layer-dialog">Layers Dialog</link>, you
          can access it through the <guimenuitem>Duplicate Layers</guimenuitem>
          command of its context menu, or by clicking on the
          <guiicon>
            <inlinemediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata
                  fileref="images/stock-icons/gimp-duplicate.svg" contentwidth="16px"/>
              </imageobject>
              <textobject>
                <phrase>Duplicate Layers</phrase>
              </textobject>
            </inlinemediaobject>
          </guiicon>
          icon button on the bottom of that dialog.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
